The paper deals with testing the equivalence between two discrete histograms, which involves statistical and information-theoretic techniques. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The problem of testing closeness of distributions is a fundamental problem in distributional testing, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves analyzing the sample complexity of the algorithm, which is a common theme in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper proposes a new algorithm that applies in a more general setting, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the sample complexity of the algorithm, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
